notesStmt.note: Title from contemporary or slightly later inscription (inside upper cover) and closing rubric (f. 91r, 92v); additional title on upper cover (in pencil in a later hand): Summolarum liber; title from opening rubric (f. 1r): Logica, sive summole.
Incipit (f. 1r): Intellectus, sive ratio, a quo homo dicitur animal rationale est facultas spiritualis a natura nobis indita ...

msContents.summary: Work on logic, by Joannes Antonius de Colis.

supportDesc.extent: 92 leaves : 196 x 136 (147 x 85) mm. bound to 205 x 136 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 92; 1-92; contemporary foliation in ink, upper right recto.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 27 long lines; ruled in drypoint.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by a single hand.

binding.p: Contemporary paper boards. Cover deteriorating at edges and spine. Lower pastedown pulling loose. Various stains and smudges. Some evidence of water damage. Small portion of the lower cover and of the adjacent book block deteriorated or eaten away, with no loss of text.

origin.p: Written in Italy in the 17th century (Zacour-Hirsch).
